16:55.968 --> 16:58.052
He never saw
the irony in that.

16:58.054 --> 17:01.555
"December 31st, 2011.

17:01.557 --> 17:05.559
"A woman calls her father
to tell him she's pregnant.

17:05.560 --> 17:08.645
says, 'Great. Thanks,'
and hangs up on her."

17:08.646 --> 17:12.098
And after pushing
her to call him,

17:12.101 --> 17:16.619
a Big Foot is discovered
in her husband's mouth.

17:17.739 --> 17:19.940
I'm glad you're
a believer, baby,

17:19.942 --> 17:24.661
but I'm never gonna believe
in an "enigma of the mystical"

17:24.663 --> 17:27.830
unless I see it
with my own eyes.

17:27.833 --> 17:29.750
Because the truth is,

17:29.752 --> 17:34.254
my father never taught me
believe in anything but myself.

17:34.256 --> 17:38.092
Well, if it helps at all,
I believe in you, too.

17:39.978 --> 17:43.013
Then there's a pretty
good chance I don't exist.

17:43.015 --> 17:44.264
How dare you?!

17:48.086 --> 17:50.354
Oh, my God!

17:50.356 --> 17:53.190
This is Robin Scherbatsky
filling in for Sandy Rivers.

17:53.192 --> 17:55.075
You know, America,

17:55.077 --> 17:58.412
tonight I've been groped,
stepped in puke

17:58.437 --> 17:59.447
and until 10 minutes ago

17:59.448 --> 18:03.500
had no idea I would be
on national television.

18:03.502 --> 18:04.718
That's my girl.

18:04.720 --> 18:07.006
But that's the magic
of New Year's.

18:07.031 --> 18:08.931
When that clock
strikes midnight,

18:08.991 --> 18:10.424
we all get a fresh start.

18:10.426 --> 18:14.595
And I don't know about you,
but I could really use one.

18:14.597 --> 18:18.465
And that magic moment
starts in ten...

18:18.467 --> 18:20.167
nine...

18:20.169 --> 18:23.487
<i>That night became a turning</i>
<i>point in Robin's career.</i>

18:26.524 --> 18:28.392
<i>But we'll get to that.</i>

18:29.477 --> 18:31.028
They're nice hats, Doug.

18:31.030 --> 18:34.014
They're wet
but they're nice.

18:34.016 --> 18:37.017
...three, two, one.

18:41.206 --> 18:43.073
And that's the story
of New Year's Eve.

18:43.075 --> 18:44.958
You know, I've been thinking

18:44.960 --> 18:47.628
that the reason I got so intense
with Lily

18:47.630 --> 18:51.131
about <i>Enigmas of the Mystical</i>
is that, well...

18:51.133 --> 18:53.250
Could you pass the pickles?

18:54.919 --> 18:57.921
...with you gone, I feel
the mystical a little less.

18:57.923 --> 19:00.090
Can you hand me the chips?

19:00.092 --> 19:02.926
Sometimes
I feel you a little less.

19:02.928 --> 19:06.713
That's why today was
so important because I just...

19:06.715 --> 19:07.881
I needed to...

19:10.718 --> 19:14.905
Did you just open a beer
on my father's headstone?

19:14.907 --> 19:16.406
Actually, it's a hard cider.

19:16.408 --> 19:19.660
<i>And just as he was about</i>
<i>to lose it...</i>

19:19.662 --> 19:21.445
Hey, Marvin, can you
pass me a burger?

19:21.447 --> 19:22.863
Hey, not Marvin. Marshall.

19:22.865 --> 19:25.232
Sorry, it's just,
you're so much like your pop.

19:25.234 --> 19:27.835
<i>Your Uncle Marshall</i>
<i>thought back</i>

19:27.837 --> 19:29.786
<i>to all those tailgates</i>
